</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D04212AB72FA1DECAD8B3B16F7797048" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9292113D0688D27DD62AD9D76B07BD0E" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="529607C03EC0209804DA373E9E6AB721" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">
This species can be recognized by the combination of the following features: medium body size (body length 23 mm); integument black, with distinct metallic green highlights on metasoma and mesosoma, particularly on mesoscutellum, and head with blue metallic highlights (Figs 
<figureCitation id="885E38FEADF15F41874AE15A0A93DE5D" captionStart="Figures 17–21" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 17 - 21. Neotype of X. dimidiata Latreille. 17 Facial view 18 Dorsal view of head and mesosoma 19 Left fore and hind wings 20 Detail of metasomal terga 21 Associated labels (NHML)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.61.20345.figures17-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174971" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">17</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="E88E8B3DE45548D3424C2809F4B26E31" captionStart="Figures 17–21" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 17 - 21. Neotype of X. dimidiata Latreille. 17 Facial view 18 Dorsal view of head and mesosoma 19 Left fore and hind wings 20 Detail of metasomal terga 21 Associated labels (NHML)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.61.20345.figures17-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174971" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0DE51E7CD942332948FBE35776B0B35A" captionStart="Figures 17–21" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 17 - 21. Neotype of X. dimidiata Latreille. 17 Facial view 18 Dorsal view of head and mesosoma 19 Left fore and hind wings 20 Detail of metasomal terga 21 Associated labels (NHML)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.61.20345.figures17-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174971" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">20</figureCitation>
); wings dark brown with violet highlights except apex green (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="490B3752C3DA25578FCDD292BB608853" captionStart="Figures 17–21" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 17 - 21. Neotype of X. dimidiata Latreille. 17 Facial view 18 Dorsal view of head and mesosoma 19 Left fore and hind wings 20 Detail of metasomal terga 21 Associated labels (NHML)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.61.20345.figures17-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174971" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">19</figureCitation>
); pubescence black; labrum basally with a distinct, large, single capitate tubercle, about as large as OD; T1 with plumose and simple setae; discs of T2 and T3 with very short, simple setae, each seta barely exiting puncture (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9CBBE2BCF74341920953AC0D11E856E0" captionStart="Figures 17–21" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 17 - 21. Neotype of X. dimidiata Latreille. 17 Facial view 18 Dorsal view of head and mesosoma 19 Left fore and hind wings 20 Detail of metasomal terga 21 Associated labels (NHML)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.61.20345.figures17-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174971" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">20</figureCitation>
); and T4-T6 with long setae, 1-2 times longer than those on T2 and T3.
</paragraph>
