<subSubSection id="AB925EC175809100C296E77B27D1B530" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" type="comments">
<paragraph id="F2C6D64AA86AC75E1B4997F78CEE7E72" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F2F1A5DD3D7460131C91B23948E026CB" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">
The identity of 
<taxonomicName id="62E492998A4A9FCB6256473B317623E5" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="2E428FF7075C7BE530824B454CEAC5ED" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">Xylocopa dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="765835C6B655977C2E7FA1F3A0FAE299" author="Latreille, PA" editor="Humboldt, A" journalOrPublisher="2. Schoell, Paris [95]" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" pagination="9 - 138" refId="B10" refString="Latreille, PA, 1809. Insectes de l'Amerique equinoxiale, recueillis pendant le voyage de MM. de Humboldt et Bonpland et decrits par M. Latreille. In: Humboldt, A, Bonpland, A, Eds., Recueil d'observations de zoologie et d' anatomie comparee, faites dans l'Ocean Atlantique, dans l'interieur du nouveau continent et dans le mer du Sud pendant les annees 1799, 1800, 1801, 1802 et 1803 Vol. 2. Schoell, Paris [95]: 9 - 138" title="Insectes de l'Amerique equinoxiale, recueillis pendant le voyage de MM. de Humboldt et Bonpland et decrits par M. Latreille." volumeTitle="Recueil d'observations de zoologie et d' anatomie comparee, faites dans l'Ocean Atlantique, dans l'interieur du nouveau continent et dans le mer du Sud pendant les annees 1799, 1800, 1801, 1802 et 1803 Vol." year="1809">Latreille (1809)</bibRefCitation>
has been a mystery and its current concept encompasses more than one species (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="50A71082E71E0C6358C30A238D51C5CD" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 22. Schematic representation of the historical changes in the species concept and nomenclature surrounding X. dimidiata Latreille (see text for details). The yellow and blue columns each represent a species concept." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.61.20345.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174972" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">22</figureCitation>
). Latreille proposed 
<taxonomicName id="2E1ACD1CACE774637230F74E17A85FB6" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="7F25EA33FF757008E70E5323E39ABFA1" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">Xylocopa dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single female collected somewhere along Alexander von Humboldt and 
<normalizedToken id="0943AEFD50456653530C5C48515F0C71" originalValue="Aimé">Aime</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="02B817903CCFF9B541BF72ADF51CDE31" originalValue="Bonpland’s">Bonpland's</normalizedToken>
voyage and whose whereabouts are unknown (
<bibRefCitation id="55B2FA0200CE0A0F35FF9748F5E2C416" author="Hurd, Jr PD" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D. C." pageId="16" pageNumber="47" refId="B6" refString="Hurd, Jr PD, 1978. An annotated catalog of the carpenter bees (genus Xylocopa Latreille) of the Western Hemisphere. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D.C." title="An annotated catalog of the carpenter bees (genus Xylocopa Latreille) of the Western Hemisphere." year="1978">Hurd 1978</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BC739D991BE4BBC444A839FF83B64D59" author="Moure, JS" editor="Moure, JS" journalOrPublisher="Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" pagination="637 - 673" publicationUrl="http://www.moure.cria.org.br/catalogue" refId="B17" refString="Moure, JS, 2007. Xylocopini Latreille, 1802. In: Moure, JS, Urban, D, Melo, GAR, Eds., Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba: 637 - 673, http://www.moure.cria.org.br/catalogue" title="Xylocopini Latreille, 1802." url="http://www.moure.cria.org.br/catalogue" volumeTitle="Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region." year="2007">Moure 2007</bibRefCitation>
). More than 60 years after 
<normalizedToken id="13E58418089DF23BCC8835AE85C23606" originalValue="Latreille’s">Latreille's</normalizedToken>
description, Smith (1874) identified and briefly described a female specimen from Ega [
<normalizedToken id="D96C2F89AE6AE6D4E97D7DD55C4B0D5B" originalValue="Tefé">Tefe</normalizedToken>
], Brazil, as what he interpreted to represent 
<taxonomicName id="54964CF73C8D024117BF232CFE40015D" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="DE267D31E901DE04260154E55F9EF204" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Latreille. Subsequent authors followed 
<normalizedToken id="270843D66D9C3022D652297B7E7D03D8" originalValue="Smith’s">Smith's</normalizedToken>
concept of 
<taxonomicName id="430B8953918F1D3A5CC0805075861112" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="F3C31E7CA215EFA8490F3D18F849B714" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and even incorrectly attributed the name to him, despite Smith making a clear reference to Latreille when using the name (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="FAE5A9719D780A56BEEB72C9BE6C6CA1" author="Schrottky, C" journalOrPublisher="Revista do Museu Paulista" pageId="17" pageNumber="48" pagination="330 - 613" refId="B22" refString="Schrottky, C, 1902. Ensaio sobre as abelhas solitarias do Brazil. Revista do Museu Paulista 5: 330 - 613" title="Ensaio sobre as abelhas solitarias do Brazil." volume="5" year="1902">Schrottky 1902</bibRefCitation>
). In fact, because 
<bibRefCitation id="0295D3E76C22C0DE2AF7B1CAA952629B" author="Cockerell, TDA" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="15" pageNumber="46" pagination="211 - 236" refId="B1" refString="Cockerell, TDA, 1907. On a collection of Australian and Asiatic bees. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 23: 211 - 236" title="On a collection of Australian and Asiatic bees." volume="23" year="1907">Cockerell (1907)</bibRefCitation>
thought that Smith had proposed 
<taxonomicName id="9C37BAEF8E43CE01C4352F89D5F46B82" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="611E5EB473737003A4ADCA525217E0E8" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 1874, which then would result in homonym with 
<normalizedToken id="2AACB43088E36AFD8D4766DBC1EE355D" originalValue="Latreille’s">Latreille's</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="A29D6C8E7D06D0DC909181B80EEBF666" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="6F1046A065171E3C2A95A2CA6CB480DA" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as with one established by 
<bibRefCitation id="CF26AA1F49F174A810300453C3CFB07E" author="Lepeletier, de Saint-Fargeau ALM" journalOrPublisher="Roret, Paris" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" refId="B11" refString="Lepeletier, de Saint-Fargeau ALM, 1841. Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Vol. 2. Hymenopteres. Roret, Paris" title="Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Vol. 2. Hymenopteres." year="1841">Lepeletier (1841)</bibRefCitation>
, he proposed to replace 
<normalizedToken id="E281582A30F2D726936BE99909A9BEAE" originalValue="Smith’s">Smith's</normalizedToken>
name with 
<taxonomicName id="CCC91B5C180F3AAAA2D0046880F526DC" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. batesi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="batesi">
<emphasis id="08AED33A4BE1B218E023BCF452E9F75A" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">X. batesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cockerell (
<bibRefCitation id="57259A34E27C5E87C5983092191ACF56" author="Hurd, Jr PD" journalOrPublisher="Pan-Pacific Entomologist" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" pagination="135 - 148" refId="B5" refString="Hurd, Jr PD, 1959. Some nomenclatorial problems in the genus Xylocopa Latreille (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). Pan-Pacific Entomologist 35 (3): 135 - 148" title="Some nomenclatorial problems in the genus Xylocopa Latreille (Hymenoptera: Apoidea)." volume="35" year="1959">Hurd 1959</bibRefCitation>
). However, because Smith (1874) did not establish a name, 
<normalizedToken id="42B16CE3C84607271D36D0BF6B6205D2" originalValue="Cockerell’s">Cockerell's</normalizedToken>
replacement name for an unavailable name is therefore invalid under the ICZN (
<emphasis id="8915E6530DE7CD83DB1D7F43AEE6A3C7" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">nomen invalidum</emphasis>
). For the same reasons, the synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="0819EE8262C0B051AE3A846BBC2BDD9D" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. batesi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="batesi">
<emphasis id="79AAA93C02C08946D95AC88C082308EF" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">X. batesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName id="93A7EAB5468EACBBD5BEE6AE17AFFA36" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="BA64841B210E510E1CD191E79BA811B3" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Latreille listed by 
<bibRefCitation id="E52E3C9C0729307F3E22814B45281769" author="Hurd, Jr PD" journalOrPublisher="University of California Publications in Entomology" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 365" refId="B7" refString="Hurd, Jr PD, Moure, JS, 1963. A classification on the large carpenter bees (Xylocopini) (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). University of California Publications in Entomology 29: 1 - 365" title="A classification on the large carpenter bees (Xylocopini) (Hymenoptera: Apoidea)." volume="29" year="1963">Hurd and Moure (1963)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="D91739E663CB72C968296FD0D5618D22" author="Hurd, Jr PD" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D. C." pageId="16" pageNumber="47" refId="B6" refString="Hurd, Jr PD, 1978. An annotated catalog of the carpenter bees (genus Xylocopa Latreille) of the Western Hemisphere. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D.C." title="An annotated catalog of the carpenter bees (genus Xylocopa Latreille) of the Western Hemisphere." year="1978">Hurd (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="045DE89A51042596CA66758276F18819" author="Moure, JS" editor="Moure, JS" journalOrPublisher="Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" pagination="637 - 673" publicationUrl="http://www.moure.cria.org.br/catalogue" refId="B17" refString="Moure, JS, 2007. Xylocopini Latreille, 1802. In: Moure, JS, Urban, D, Melo, GAR, Eds., Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba: 637 - 673, http://www.moure.cria.org.br/catalogue" title="Xylocopini Latreille, 1802." url="http://www.moure.cria.org.br/catalogue" volumeTitle="Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region." year="2007">Moure (2007)</bibRefCitation>
are unavailable.
</paragraph>
<caption id="D53DEAF51C6B416EE157F7691DBC72F6" ID-Zenodo-Dep="1138968" doi="10.3897/jhr.61.20345.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174972" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" start="Figure 22" startId="F8">
<paragraph id="A4B0D44E29F4819B90EAB6F4F9743A57" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="223F53287A8DB0B406CDB5561969D567" bold="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">Figure 22.</emphasis>
Schematic representation of the historical changes in the species concept and nomenclature surrounding 
<taxonomicName id="462EFA91C5748E34769637D5A405B6C4" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="A4C6B0D58525722217BADA64565BAC5E" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="43">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Latreille (see text for details). The yellow and blue columns each represent a species concept.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E5DD0AE13E8FDB20F63C888CB50C6420" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="13" pageNumber="44">
<pageBreakToken id="4F2A115093A8D7C1802ED28DB8B991AD" pageId="13" pageNumber="44" start="start">The</pageBreakToken>
specimen identified as 
<taxonomicName id="65DB3DF358EF0B9CD5D64E4B4238D2AC" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="44" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="EB93275F9F183F75381EC2E76ADBC451" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="44">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Smith is in the NHML (Figs 
<figureCitation id="A43A61144AE9EF24AC6E9E1532DEA1AC" captionStart="Figures 23–26" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 23 - 26. Specimen of the NHML identified as X. dimidiata Latreille by F. Smith. 23 Facial view 24 Dorsal view of head 25 Detail of terga 26 Associated locality and determination labels (Photographs by David Notton, NHML)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.61.20345.figures23-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174973" pageId="13" pageNumber="44">23-26</figureCitation>
), along with the specimen from the same locality herein designated as the neotype of that species. The second specimen is in better condition than that identified by Smith and, judging by the handwriting of the labels, it appears to be from the same collection event. Given the confusing identity of 
<taxonomicName id="8914B1C4D2A194B17CCF40FB131E7D96" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="44" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="21CA8FC15EC3F3BF50C36DCDF105DB07" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="44">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the designation of a neotype is necessary to stabilize the name. For practical reasons, we chose as the neotype a specimen that matches 
<normalizedToken id="74621128F5EFDAB55A700069AD1EC82B" originalValue="Smith’s">Smith's</normalizedToken>
concept of 
<taxonomicName id="7994622CD1DCF2E5DF27298B835FD8A2" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="44" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="CE50DED3D36A53D0D2657E8277D9299B" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="44">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Latreille. Although this proposed taxonomic action resolves the identity issue of 
<taxonomicName id="480B3100012201796E962CEC0167A570" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="44" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="E433920DDD00A752AB6E0A99A41A3F44" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="44">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there is no reason to assume that 
<normalizedToken id="F205D81ECF67C54A69B3802672B620FB" originalValue="Smith’s">Smith's</normalizedToken>
interpretation of 
<normalizedToken id="DAAB1A9565886A02A9BF41D90CE9AD7F" originalValue="Latreille’s">Latreille's</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="1394018DF8531D3C8B5F8E0EF39EA29A" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="44" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="D8AAE6251B745DA1DDD9064EACBA5882" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="44">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is correct. First, 
<normalizedToken id="1F7F30A60855E0045C5C751AF3F57F50" originalValue="Smith’s">Smith's</normalizedToken>
specimen is from the Amazon Basin, in a locality well outside of the route taken by Humboldt and Bonpland. These explorers traveled through large areas of Venezuela and the Magdalena River Valley in Colombia and through the Andes southward to Lima, Peru, and Guayaquil, Ecuador, before traveling to Mexico (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="C6D299AC7473DA23DA2BA0E396CFC416" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4107508" author="Sandwith, NY" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information" pageId="17" pageNumber="48" pagination="295 - 310" refId="B20" refString="Sandwith, NY, 1925. Humboldt and Bonpland's itinerary in Venezuela. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information 7: 295 - 310, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4107508" title="Humboldt and Bonpland's itinerary in Venezuela." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4107508" volume="7" year="1925">Sandwith 1925</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="3636A765784CBA6F39DFC929B4E634A9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4118688" author="Sandwith, NY" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information" pageId="17" pageNumber="48" pagination="181 - 190" refId="B21" refString="Sandwith, NY, 1926. Humboldt and Bonpland's itinerary in Ecuador and Peru. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information 4: 181 - 190, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4118688" title="Humboldt and Bonpland's itinerary in Ecuador and Peru." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4118688" volume="4" year="1926">1926</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CD1DCED183942C6691BBAA2CFFC06A4D" author="Papavero, N" journalOrPublisher="Museu de Zoologia, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" refId="B18" refString="Papavero, N, 1971. Essays on the history of Neotropical Dipterology, with special reference to the collectors (1750-1905). Vol. 1. Museu de Zoologia, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo" title="Essays on the history of Neotropical Dipterology, with special reference to the collectors (1750 - 1905). Vol. 1." year="1971">Papavero 1971</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, 
<normalizedToken id="CED9D3BD76FC71EF3B292A4A0917C952" originalValue="Latreille’s">Latreille's</normalizedToken>
specimen could have been collected from any of these areas bordering the Amazon Basin, unless it came from San Carlos de 
<normalizedToken id="34E075687F2A5228A47A97C07CD3CDFC" originalValue="Río">Rio</normalizedToken>
Negro in 
<normalizedToken id="93EF24195D7648670690376104C0395E" originalValue="Venezuela’s">Venezuela's</normalizedToken>
Amazonas state. Second, specimens standing in collections under 
<taxonomicName id="4BCC3AAD3D6E99F1B3201BBAD4FFDB31" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="44" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="685AADDFF041DC00CF46FC4D2897AF55" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="44">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
actually belong to multiple species, distinct from 
<normalizedToken id="11DC62D84BDF0D6BC623C1B16DF23BD1" originalValue="Smith’s">Smith's</normalizedToken>
material. This is the case for the Bolivian specimens described 
<pageBreakToken id="35728917A8BF0AF689243DECE3BF9519" pageId="14" pageNumber="45" start="start">herein</pageBreakToken>
as new (
<taxonomicName id="278904EA7E39CC416E08DE9488E6D6F3" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. barbarae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="barbarae">
<emphasis id="D1D5537D04D283FE3B17B4A34675471D" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">X. barbarae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), which superficially fall within the historical concept of 
<normalizedToken id="B70898F0EB5C49ED1D444B54D8FAFA60" originalValue="Smith’s">Smith's</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="62B1C499927C719675F11902D0F04757" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="580B1A7D02D89B241B50677D0044008C" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differing in the longer and denser pubescence of terga, presence of white setae on sides of T2-T4, and wings with violet highlights throughout. Thus, 
<normalizedToken id="A4A82B44E343D427D0A386178B18E9E1" originalValue="Smith’s">Smith's</normalizedToken>
concept of 
<normalizedToken id="5FF3ABAA75B3EA60BA203D1FDA9D33EA" originalValue="Latreille’s">Latreille's</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="3A6CE7194B69EF2F12FC555C5E1A794F" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="DC980A05EBD7823EBBFEB87F920EAC7E" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is questionable, and the current application of this name includes several species.
</paragraph>
<caption id="122C3713F9F979CC4D88505682FF014A" ID-Zenodo-Dep="1138978" doi="10.3897/jhr.61.20345.figures23-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/174973" pageId="14" pageNumber="45" start="Figures 23–26" startId="F9">
<paragraph id="2C49F5D5F246575B01E2A37E56AEFF44" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="14B19B56F3E7267064C5EAF6FE964ED7" bold="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">Figures 23-26.</emphasis>
Specimen of the NHML identified as 
<taxonomicName id="DA8B8B4B14F038B637197CE422BE0F6F" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="9D9544231BE06A2EC82B83CEBC2826AA" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Latreille by F. Smith. 
<emphasis id="A5DD5A5FDCD55F2911B42C4C5A7924F9" bold="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">23</emphasis>
Facial view 
<emphasis id="B5F7D82BC76DDA543EF0B266443B412C" bold="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">24</emphasis>
Dorsal view of head 
<emphasis id="6A94DE84CCA2DC893876E6C9AD3F6777" bold="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">25</emphasis>
Detail of terga 
<emphasis id="3120D09B0FDE854266D25E180051F6A2" bold="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">26</emphasis>
Associated locality and determination labels (Photographs by David Notton, NHML).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="67B9F9C393BFED7337A306FE7E34620C" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">
Given the problems outlined above, we initially thought that it would be best to regard 
<taxonomicName id="089C6FC621C1B200FD12B63942C2777F" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="D825D554AC2896EBBACAB3491CD66CAA" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Latreille as a 
<emphasis id="77CD4BC193185BBC1CCA91D0BE044E24" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">nomen dubium</emphasis>
, meaning that future workers would have the task to fix this name to one of those biological species overlapping Humboldt and 
<normalizedToken id="237FBC53011813D240A27119F5C0255C" originalValue="Bonpland’s">Bonpland's</normalizedToken>
route. 
<taxonomicName id="7BDBA5CF4E0FA6955B95395D57D00B8E" authority="" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa (Schonnherria)" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Schonnherria">Xylocopa (Schonnherria)</taxonomicName>
is the second most species-rich group of 
<taxonomicName id="AFEC2F6ECDE9335F3549B86D9774F99D" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DA8E85A624B761B4D2852FF3F5C17825" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">Xylocopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Western Hemisphere, containing about 30 species ranging from southern United States to southern Argentina (
<bibRefCitation id="1C43D73CA7623AE9C3B9E635BA1B5902" author="Michener, CD" journalOrPublisher="The Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" refId="B15" refString="Michener, CD, 2007. The Bees of the World [2nd Edn]. The Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore" title="The Bees of the World [2 nd Edn]." year="2007">Michener 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Because taxonomic issues like these are best resolved in a context of a revision, a study of such a magnitude might take several years to complete, if done at all. Thus, despite all problems surrounding the identity of 
<taxonomicName id="1AFB9FB908A2B0458958E371E2AE8A10" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="F971D0DB239C681492021E2B33DABCC7" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we chose to designate a neotype for this species following 
<normalizedToken id="E1D97588554FB9254DB2C67CC3B97432" originalValue="Smith’s">Smith's</normalizedToken>
interpretation. This might not be 
<normalizedToken id="F23F000794DE5EFA4A3F37AA58C55BE6" originalValue="Latreille’s">Latreille's</normalizedToken>
concept of 
<taxonomicName id="3D08D8C57FFAE94B7D2CC79AAEF71E97" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="5225E3F9D48A3012BD1AF832211D79FB" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but we believe this taxonomic action now would be beneficial to the advancement of the taxonomy of the group. The label data for the specimen here designated as the neotype are as follows: 5669 / Ega / 5669 / Ega / Neotype, 
<taxonomicName id="72B3884A4C4F1C7C5182C353CA95F062" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa dimidiata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="8146D878D783158A1DDDA6B9B78CD2D5" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="45">Xylocopa dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Latreille des. M. Lucia V.H. Gonzalez ♀.
</paragraph>
